Author: @antisensocomum8188
Comment: Eu prefiro um jogo mais realista, tanto em destruição, quanto dirigibilidade dos veículos. O GTA 5 peca muito em destruição, quando 2 carros se batem em alta velocidade, falta impacto, falta peso, dano e sensação de colisão, parecem 2 carros de plástico super leves batendo. E quanto a dirigilidade, prefiro mais realista, mas não necessariamente muito realista, até pra tornar o jogo mais dinâmico. Em resumo, o jogo pune muito pouco a má pilotagem, isso tira a imersão, porque quando você erra, você bate num muro a 100km/h e volta a pilotar como se nada tivesse acontecido... Invés de você detonar com o carro numa batida dessas... Você salta rampas e cai de centenas de metros sem ter impacto nenhum no carro... E por aí vai. Não gosto desse lado arcade porque tira muita imersão e cuidado do jogador.

Author: @ToddFreeman85
Comment:
I wish YT had a filter for reaction videos, or some way for me to block them. More often than not, I'd rather watch the original video, and I end up feeling tricked and pissed off when I realize I've been duped into watching some asshole add their two cents over top of the thing I really want to watch.

If you are being taken advantage of by a reaction channel that won't work with you, strike them. The respect has to flow both ways mate, otherwise you're just allowing these parasites to feed off you (which will only encourage more people to do the same).

Think about it. If your channel gains a reputation for being compassionate towards these kinds of behaviors, then your channel will become a target for more and more of this sort of exploitation.

Go watch some videos of extreme botfly removals if you need some motivation. At a certain point, there may be so many of these channels that you might be unable to compete with them, and then you'll struggle to find the will to continue.

Lastly, I would recommend not investing a lot of emotion or expectation in the result of copyright strikes. It's possible YT will not side with you, so I'd develop a template you can reuse as often as possible so that you're not wasting too much time. Hopefully, you'll be at a level soon that will enable you to have access to a team that will handle this sort of thing for you.

Cheers, and best of luck with getting rid of these blood sucking ticks ;)
